Hi, i met the same issue in Win7x64, when i read an image,

import tensorflow as tf
image_filename = "./1.jpg"
filename_queue = tf.train.string_input_producer(
    tf.train.match_filenames_once(image_filename)
)
image_reader = tf.WholeFileReader()
_, image_file = image_reader.read(filename_queue)
image = tf.image.decode_jpeg(image_file)
sess=tf.InteractiveSession()
print(sess.run(image))

body:
@kindlychung  @yaroslavvb 
Hi, i met the same issue in Win7x64, when i read an image, 

```python
import tensorflow as tf
image_filename = "./1.jpg"
filename_queue = tf.train.string_input_producer(
    tf.train.match_filenames_once(image_filename)
)
image_reader = tf.WholeFileReader()
_, image_file = image_reader.read(filename_queue)
image = tf.image.decode_jpeg(image_file)
sess=tf.InteractiveSession()
print(sess.run(image))

```
The console show the log:
```log
>py imgload.py
Tensor("ReaderReadV2:1", shape=(), dtype=string)
2018-05-18 10:03:39.221544: I C:\tf_jenkins\workspace\tf-nightly-windows\M\windo
ws\PY\36\tensorflow\core\platform\cpu_feature_guard.cc:140] Your CPU supports in
structions that this TensorFlow binary was not compiled to use: AVX2
```

The console has no responsive any more.
